  <!-- UNDER THE HOOD -->
  <section class="tt-explain">
    <div class="tt-explain-head">
      <p class="section-eyebrow">Under the hood</p>
      <h2 class="tt-explain-title">What you just watched,<br><em>and why it maps to my desk</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="tt-explain-grid">
      <div class="tt-ex">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">01</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">Source</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">Tool-using agents pull filings, price, and news in parallel. At CIBC I built and maintained a 600+ security convertible bond database and ran the daily data pulls behind it. Sourcing clean inputs is the unglamorous half of the job.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-ex">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">02</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">Analyze</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">Three agents argue bull, bear, and catalyst at once. I train frontier models at Handshake AI, engineering rubrics to find where they fail. Making several agents disagree on purpose, then judging the output, is exactly that skill.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-ex">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">03</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">Score</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">A transparent weighted model, not a black box. You see fundamentals, valuation, catalyst, moat, and risk, and how they roll into one conviction number. I priced 30+ equity-linked trades off vol surfaces and credit spreads. Numbers you cannot defend are worthless.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-ex">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">04</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">Brief</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">The memo drafts in my house style: warm but serious, direct, quantified, no em dashes. At CIBC I wrote 40+ daily market commentaries for IB and Sales. The agent drafts. A human decides. It never auto-trades.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-ex">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">05</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">Track</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">Every idea is logged and re-scored, so you watch conviction move over time. A CRM for theses. Being early is only worth something if you write it down, date it, and hold yourself to it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tt-ex tt-ex-arch">
        <p class="tt-ex-n">·</p>
        <h3 class="tt-ex-h">The architecture</h3>
        <p class="tt-ex-b">Multi-agent orchestration, tool use, structured output, and a human-in-the-loop guardrail: draft only, never auto-execute. Built on the same skills-based agent system as my job-search engine. The wedge is not that I use AI. It is that I build it and still own the fundamentals to catch its mistakes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="tt-disclaimer">
      Illustrative demo for portfolio purposes. Snapshot figures are approximate and dated, not live market data, and nothing here is investment advice.
    </p>
  </section>

